Spatial operations on vector data

Spatial subsetting

# subset nz by attribute
#
canterbury = nz %>% filter(Name == "Canterbury")

# subset nz_height by polygon intersection
#
canterbury_height = nz_height[canterbury, , op = st_intersects ]
tmap_mode("view")
## tmap mode set to interactive viewing
tm_basemap("OpenStreetMap") +
  tm_shape(canterbury) + tm_borders() +
  tm_shape(canterbury_height) + tm_dots(col = "red", size = 0.05)
# use geometry as a stencil to pull stuff out of another dataset.

Topological relations

(see Geometric binary predicates on pairs of simple feature geometry sets)

# create a polygon
#
a_poly = st_polygon(list(rbind(c(-1, -1), c(1, -1), c(1, 1), c(-1, -1))))
a = st_sfc(a_poly)

# create a line
#
l_line = st_linestring(x = matrix(c(-1, -1, -0.5, 1), ncol = 2))
l = st_sfc(l_line)

# create points
#
p_matrix = matrix(c(0.5, 1, -1, 0, 0, 1, 0.5, 1), ncol = 2)
p_multi = st_multipoint(x = p_matrix)
p = st_cast(st_sfc(p_multi), "POINT")
plot(a, col = "gray")
plot(l, add = TRUE)
plot(p, add = TRUE)
text(st_coordinates(p)[,1], st_coordinates(p)[,2], seq_along(p), pos = 4)

st_intersects(p, a)
## Sparse geometry binary predicate list of length 4, where the predicate
## was `intersects'
##  1: 1
##  2: 1
##  3: (empty)
##  4: (empty)
st_disjoint(p, a)
## Sparse geometry binary predicate list of length 4, where the predicate
## was `disjoint'
##  1: (empty)
##  2: (empty)
##  3: 1
##  4: 1
st_within(p, a)
## Sparse geometry binary predicate list of length 4, where the predicate
## was `within'
##  1: 1
##  2: (empty)
##  3: (empty)
##  4: (empty)
st_touches(p, a)
## Sparse geometry binary predicate list of length 4, where the predicate
## was `touches'
##  1: (empty)
##  2: 1
##  3: (empty)
##  4: (empty)
st_is_within_distance(p, a, dist = 0.9)
## Sparse geometry binary predicate list of length 4, where the predicate
## was `is_within_distance'
##  1: 1
##  2: 1
##  3: (empty)
##  4: 1

Spatial joining

# random number generator seed
# (use constant for reproducibility)
#
set.seed(2018)

# world bounding box
#
(bb_world = st_bbox(world))
##       xmin       ymin       xmax       ymax 
## -180.00000  -89.90000  179.99999   83.64513
random_df = tibble(
  x = runif(n = 10, min = bb_world[1], max = bb_world[3]),
  y = runif(n = 10, min = bb_world[2], max = bb_world[4])
)

(random_points = random_df %>%
    st_as_sf(coords = c("x", "y")) %>%
    st_set_crs(4326))
## Simple feature collection with 10 features and 0 fields
## Geometry type: POINT
## Dimension:     XY
## Bounding box:  xmin: -158.1893 ymin: -42.91501 xmax: 165.1157 ymax: 80.5408
## Geodetic CRS:  WGS 84
## # A tibble: 10  1
##                 geometry
##  *           <POINT []>
##  1 (-58.98475 -21.24278)
##  2  (-13.05963 25.42744)
##  3   (-158.1893 80.5408)
##  4  (-108.9239 27.80098)
##  5   (-9.246895 49.9822)
##  6  (-71.62251 20.15883)
##  7  (38.43318 -42.91501)
##  8  (-133.1956 6.053818)
##  9   (165.1157 38.16862)
## 10   (16.86581 53.86485)
world_random = world[random_points,]

  tm_dots(col = "red", size = 0.1) +

Non-overlapping joins

tmap_mode("view")
## tmap mode set to interactive viewing
tm_shape(cycle_hire) +
  tm_dots(size = 0.05, alpha = 0.5, col = "blue") +
  tm_shape(cycle_hire_osm) +
  tm_dots(size = 0.05, alpha = 0.5, col = "red")
any(st_touches(cycle_hire, cycle_hire_osm, sparse = FALSE))
## [1] FALSE
st_crs(cycle_hire)$Name
## [1] "WGS 84"
st_crs(cycle_hire_osm)$Name
## [1] "WGS 84"
st_crs(27700)$Name
## [1] "OSGB 1936 / British National Grid"
cycle_hire_P     = st_transform(cycle_hire,     27700)
cycle_hire_osm_P = st_transform(cycle_hire_osm, 27700)

sel = st_is_within_distance(cycle_hire_P, cycle_hire_osm_P, dist = 20)

summary(lengths(sel) > 0)
##    Mode   FALSE    TRUE 
## logical     304     438
z = st_join(cycle_hire_P, cycle_hire_osm_P,
            join = st_is_within_distance, dist = 20)

nrow(cycle_hire)
## [1] 742
nrow(z)
## [1] 762
z = z %>% 
  group_by(id) %>% 
  summarize(capacity = mean(capacity))

nrow(z) == nrow(cycle_hire)
## [1] TRUE
plot(cycle_hire_osm["capacity"])

plot(z["capacity"])

Spatial data aggregation

nz_avheight = aggregate(x = nz_height, by = nz, FUN = mean)

nz_avheight2 = nz %>%
  st_join(nz_height) %>%
  group_by(Name) %>%
  summarize(elevation = mean(elevation, na.rm = TRUE))

tmap_mode("plot")
## tmap mode set to plotting
tm_shape(nz_avheight) +
  tm_fill(col = "elevation")

tm_shape(nz_avheight2) +
  tm_fill(col = "elevation")

Distance relations

nz_heighest = nz_height %>% top_n(n = 1, wt = elevation)
canterbury_centroid = st_centroid(canterbury)
## Warning in st_centroid.sf(canterbury): st_centroid assumes attributes are
## constant over geometries of x
st_distance(nz_heighest, canterbury_centroid)
## Units: [m]
##        [,1]
## [1,] 115540
co = filter(nz, grepl("Canter|Otag", Name))
st_distance(nz_height[1:3, ], co)
## Units: [m]
##           [,1]     [,2]
## [1,] 123537.16 15497.72
## [2,]  94282.77     0.00
## [3,]  93018.56     0.00
